    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-10-28T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-28T09:00:00-05:00" n="550"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d550">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.24112 RP/19: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Boal</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">La Paz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-28T10:00:00-04:00"
                            >October 28, 1943—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 12:58 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1705. The Bolivian Senate yesterday rejected a draft law which would have removed
                    from economic warfare sanctions certain Axis subjects with long residence in
                    Bolivia or with Bolivian children. The text of this proposed law was transmitted
                    to the Department with despatch No. 2249 of September 17.<note n="56"
                        xml:id="d550fn56">Not printed; but see telegram No. 1369, August 14, <ref
                            target="#pg_602">p. 602</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Boal</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
